            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>paneer cubes</strong> to a large bowl with the <strong>chopped pepper</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>(save the rest for later!) and a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>marinated paneer & pepper</strong></p><p>Thread the <strong>marinated paneer & pepper</strong> onto the <strong>soaked skewers</strong> and transfer them to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 13-15 min or until the paneer is slightly charred – these are your <strong>paneer & pepper skewers</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>chicken breast portions </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1657003588891-x200.jpg",
