            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped chicken</strong>, the <strong>curry powder </strong>and the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and cook for 2 min further or until fragrant</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>ground</strong> <strong>almonds </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 10-12 min further or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once the chicken is cooked through, add the <strong>cultured coconut</strong> – this is your <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>chicken pasanda</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
